This player plays modules with identifier 6CHN/8CHN. Module type is essentially
the same as protracker except it supports also 6 and 8 channel modules.

Configuration:

  @{b}Mixingrate@{ub}  - defines the rate of mixing. The bigger the value the better
                    the sound quality. In theory this works like this, but
                    of course if the samples have been taken with small
                    sampling rate this can't make them any better.

  @{b}Volboost@{ub}    - Volume boost value.

  @{b}Playmodes@{ub}
        See @{"Playmodes" link EPLplaymodes}


    NOTE: Always use "Reloc >Fast" flag with this player, otherwise
    playing will take more CPU power when accessing CHIP memory bus.


